    <descript>
      <abstract>This point feature contains water structures & corresponding information that falls within the boundary of Loudoun County.</abstract>
      <purpose>To provide spatially correct location & information for water structures within Loudoun County.</purpose>
      <supplinf>Data are stored in the corporate ArcSDE Geodatabase as a point feature class.  The coordinate system is Virginia State Plane (North), Zone 4501, datum NAD83 HARN (vertical datum, if applicable, NAVD88), US Survey foot units

LCSA (Loudoun County Sanitary Authority) provides two Datasets to Loudoun County Office of Mapping & Geographic Information (OMAGI): Waste water and Water to OMAGI.  These two datasets are combined and four new datasets created from the source data: Wastewater_Line, Wastewater_Point, Water_Line, & Water_Point.</supplinf>
    </descript>

      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Water structures feature class derived from source Water dataset & feature classes wControlValve, wHydrant, wPumpStation, wTank, wTreatmentPlant, wValve, and wVault

- Create a new field called LCSAType in each source feature class to identify type of structure
- Populate the new field in each source feature class with the appropriate type value; Control Valve, Hydrant, Pump Station, Tank, Treatment Plant, Valve, Vault
- Union all source feature classes together to produce new LCSA_WATER_POINT feature class
- Remove all attribute fields except for LifecycleStatus, Owner, LocationDescrip, LCSAType, wType, Comment, TankName, StationName, PlantName, & VaultName</procdesc>
